rooked nose’, and in the Lowlands is apparently an assimilated form of a Norman baronial name derived from Cambernon in Normandy. It is very popular as a boy's name, and now also occurs as a girl's name ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kameron","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which in the Highlands is derived from Gaelic <i>cam sròn</i> ‘crooked nose’, and in the Lowlands is apparently an assimilated form of a Norman baronial name derived from Cambernon in Normandy. It is very popular as a boy's name, and now also occurs as a girl's name ."]},{"name":"Camron","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which in the Highlands is derived from Gaelic <i>cam sròn</i> ‘crooked nose’, and in the Lowlands is apparently an assimilated form of a Norman baronial name derived from Cambernon in Normandy. It is very popular as a boy's name, and now also occurs as a girl's name ."]},{"name":"Kamran","meanings":["Fanciful respelling of   Cameron ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":19,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":28,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705189,"age":63,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict bet